-{"id":"bd-3aciu","title":"task(pane-state): integrate persistence lifecycle into terminal and web runtimes","description":"Wire pane state persistence into runtime lifecycle (load, save, autosave, explicit export/import) for both terminal and web.\n\nDeliverables\n- Runtime hooks for initial layout load and dirty-state save.\n- Autosave policy with debounce and failure handling.\n- Host-specific storage adapters (filesystem/localStorage/etc).\n\nAcceptance\n- Users can resume pane layouts reliably after restart.\n- Save/load failures do not corrupt active session state.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Implement scoped persistence/history/recovery behavior with explicit schema/version handling.\n2) Add unit tests for migration, undo/redo semantics, recovery, and import/export round-trips.\n3) Validate deterministic outputs for canonical state corpora.\n4) Ensure recovery and migration logs include version/source, decisions, and resulting state checksum.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WindyBeaver","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:34:03.426799709Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:01:53.308019537Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["pane","persistence","runtime","state"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1381a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1efcv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1wg6i","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1100,"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","author":"WindyBeaver","text":"Progress 2026-04-25: hardened terminal/demo pane workspace filesystem writer. Root cause: the save helper used a predictable sibling *.tmp path, so stale temp files or concurrent writers could clobber or steal each other's temp file before rename. Fix: writes now reserve a unique sibling temp file with create_new, retry name collisions, and only acknowledge the pane workspace generation after successful rename. Added regression coverage proving the legacy *.tmp path is not overwritten.","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:01:53Z"}]}
+{"id":"bd-3aciu","title":"task(pane-state): integrate persistence lifecycle into terminal and web runtimes","description":"Wire pane state persistence into runtime lifecycle (load, save, autosave, explicit export/import) for both terminal and web.\n\nDeliverables\n- Runtime hooks for initial layout load and dirty-state save.\n- Autosave policy with debounce and failure handling.\n- Host-specific storage adapters (filesystem/localStorage/etc).\n\nAcceptance\n- Users can resume pane layouts reliably after restart.\n- Save/load failures do not corrupt active session state.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Implement scoped persistence/history/recovery behavior with explicit schema/version handling.\n2) Add unit tests for migration, undo/redo semantics, recovery, and import/export round-trips.\n3) Validate deterministic outputs for canonical state corpora.\n4) Ensure recovery and migration logs include version/source, decisions, and resulting state checksum.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WindyBeaver","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:34:03.426799709Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:24:56.206776450Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["pane","persistence","runtime","state"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1381a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1efcv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","depends_on_id":"bd-1wg6i","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1100,"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","author":"WindyBeaver","text":"Progress 2026-04-25: hardened terminal/demo pane workspace filesystem writer. Root cause: the save helper used a predictable sibling *.tmp path, so stale temp files or concurrent writers could clobber or steal each other's temp file before rename. Fix: writes now reserve a unique sibling temp file with create_new, retry name collisions, and only acknowledge the pane workspace generation after successful rename. Added regression coverage proving the legacy *.tmp path is not overwritten.","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:01:53Z"},{"id":1101,"issue_id":"bd-3aciu","author":"WindyBeaver","text":"Progress 2026-04-25: hardened web pane workspace localStorage persistence against overlay-sync failures. Root cause: the HTML host tied durable save/restore to paneOverlaySyncFailed, so one visual overlay/state snapshot failure could permanently stop autosaves even while runner export/import/ack APIs still worked. Fix: persistence and restore now depend on the runner persistence APIs directly, export failures schedule retry instead of disabling overlay sync, sync failure paths still attempt a save, and dirty/active-pointer checks fall back to runner generation/saved-generation/pointer APIs when overlay state is unavailable. Landed in 5804dd62.","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:24:56Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3ae1y","title":"E2E: PTY canonicalization integration script with JSONL logs","description":"Scope: add an E2E script that runs pty_canonicalize with real PTY fixtures, capturing normalized output into JSONL logs. Rationale: ensure PTY normalization is stable and covered end-to-end.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Script runs pty_canonicalize with recorded PTY input fixtures.\n2) JSONL logs include schema_version, input_id, mode, dims (if applicable), hash, timing, and error records.\n3) Hashes stable across runs.\n4) Fail fast on schema/hash mismatch with diagnostics.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-04T19:17:46.750686310Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-04T23:21:56.547299821Z","closed_at":"2026-02-04T23:21:56.547282719Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","logging","pty"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3ae1y","depends_on_id":"bd-22n80","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3ae1y","depends_on_id":"bd-2txo","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3ae1y","depends_on_id":"bd-3isi7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3ag2","title":"Fix queueing scheduler tick time accounting","description":"Scheduler tick advances current_time before processing, inflating response time stats and aging when multiple jobs complete in one tick. Update tick to advance time incrementally per processed segment and compute response time at completion time.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-04T05:45:54.804544206Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-04T05:47:53.878929105Z","closed_at":"2026-02-04T05:47:53.878911753Z","close_reason":"QueueingScheduler::tick now advances time incrementally per processed segment, so response-time stats/aging reflect actual completion times. Preserved overall time advance.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-3akdb","title":"epic(graveyard-§8.15): Incremental View Maintenance for Derived Render State","description":"IVM: maintain computed layouts, styled text, visibility flags as materialized views updated by deltas only. EV=5.6 (Tier A). Updates as signed tuples (key, weight, logical_time). Compile view into DAG of delta operators. Process topologically in micro-batches. Apply to: style resolution, computed layout, filtered/sorted widget lists. Fallback: full recompute. Risk: complexity (S16.5). Baseline: full recompute per frame.

**User Value:** Theme changes, style updates, and layout reflows propagate incrementally instead of triggering full recomputation, making large UIs feel instant.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Delta-propagation DAG designed for style/layout pipeline
- IncrementalView trait implemented with at least 2 concrete views
- Benchmark shows >3x speedup vs full recompute on theme change
- Correctness: incremental result == full recompute result
- All existing tests pass","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T21:47:18.212911986Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-05T18:37:10.408684313Z","closed_at":"2026-03-05T18:37:10.408663774Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["graveyard","incremental","performance","ring2"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3akdb","depends_on_id":"bd-3p4y1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:32Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
